data.name: PSet.Name[0$C8Y0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingFunctionGCurve

data.name: PSet.Definition[0$C8Y0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: Tripping functions are applied to electronic tripping units (i.e. tripping units having type property sets for electronic tripping defined). They are not applied to thermal, thermal magnetic or RCD tripping units.This property set represent the ground fault protection (G-curve) of an electronic protection device

data.name: Property.IsSelectable.Name[12n0_0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: IsSelectable

data.name: Property.IsSelectable.Definition[12n0_0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: Indication whether the S-function can be switched off or not.

data.name: Property.NominalCurrentAdjusted.Name[1AWxG0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: NominalCurrentAdjusted

data.name: Property.NominalCurrentAdjusted.Definition[1AWxG0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: An indication if the tripping currents of the short time protection is related to the nominal current multiplied with the actual setting of the current adjustment, if any, of the long time protection part of the protective device, or not.

data.name: Property.ExternalAdjusted.Name[1H4Yk0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: ExternalAdjusted

data.name: Property.ExternalAdjusted.Definition[1H4Yk0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: An indication if the ground fault protection may be adjusted according to an external current coil or not.

data.name: Property.ReleaseCurrent.Name[1N20o0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: ReleaseCurrent

data.name: Property.ReleaseCurrent.Definition[1N20o0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The release current in [x In] for the initial tripping of the S-function.

data.name: Property.ReleaseTime.Name[1RpC20qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: ReleaseTime

data.name: Property.ReleaseTime.Definition[1RpC20qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The release time in [s] for the initial tripping of the relevant part. This time indicates that for current lower than the indicated release current, the tripping time will be longer than the indicated release time. The value is given as a mean value.

data.name: Property.CurrentTolerance1.Name[1Xmg60qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: CurrentTolerance1

data.name: Property.CurrentTolerance1.Definition[1Xmg60qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The tolerance for the current of time/current-curve in [%].

data.name: Property.CurrentToleranceLimit1.Name[1d7_m0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: CurrentToleranceLimit1

data.name: Property.CurrentToleranceLimit1.Definition[1d7_m0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The time limit in [s] limiting the application of CurrentTolerance1, if any. If the value is set to 0, the value of the CurrentTolerance1 is valid for the whole time/current-curve.

data.name: Property.CurrentTolerance2.Name[1j5Sq0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: CurrentTolerance2

data.name: Property.CurrentTolerance2.Definition[1j5Sq0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The tolerance for the current of time/current-curve in [%] valid for times above CurrentTolereanceLimit1.

data.name: Property.IsCurrentTolerancePositiveOnly.Name[1pf4I0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: IsCurrentTolerancePositiveOnly

data.name: Property.IsCurrentTolerancePositiveOnly.Definition[1pf4I0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: Indication whether the value of CurrentTolerance1 is provided as a positive tolereance only or not. If not, the value is proved as a pluss/minus tolerance.

data.name: Property.TimeTolerance1.Name[1wChm0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: TimeTolerance1

data.name: Property.TimeTolerance1.Definition[1wChm0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The tolerance for the time of time/current-curve in [%].

data.name: Property.TimeToleranceLimit1.Name[20A9q0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: TimeToleranceLimit1

data.name: Property.TimeToleranceLimit1.Definition[20A9q0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The current limit in [x In] limiting the application of TimeTolerance1, if any. If the value is set to 0, the value of the TimeTolerance1 is valid for the whole time/current-curve.

data.name: Property.TimeTolerance2.Name[24xL40qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: TimeTolerance2

data.name: Property.TimeTolerance2.Definition[24xL40qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The tolerance for the time of the time/current-curve in [%] valid for currents above TimeToleranceLimit1.

data.name: Property.IsTimeTolerancePositiveOnly.Name[2Aup80qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: IsTimeTolerancePositiveOnly

data.name: Property.IsTimeTolerancePositiveOnly.Definition[2Aup80qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: Indication whether the value of TimeTolerance1 is provided as a positive tolereance only or not. If not, the value is proved as a pluss/minus tolerance.

data.name: Property.ReleaseCurrentI2tStart.Name[2HSQc0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: ReleaseCurrentI2tStart

data.name: Property.ReleaseCurrentI2tStart.Definition[2HSQc0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The release current in [x In] for the start point of the I2t tripping curve of the G-function, if any.

data.name: Property.ReleaseTimeI2tStart.Name[2MplG0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: ReleaseTimeI2tStart

data.name: Property.ReleaseTimeI2tStart.Definition[2MplG0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The release time in [s] for the start point of the I2t tripping curve of the G-function, if any.

data.name: Property.ReleaseCurrentI2tEnd.Name[2SB3w0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: ReleaseCurrentI2tEnd

data.name: Property.ReleaseCurrentI2tEnd.Definition[2SB3w0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The release current in [x In] for the end point of the I2t tripping curve of the G-function, if any. The value of ReleaseCurrentI2tEnd shall be larger than ReleaseCurrentI2tStart.

data.name: Property.ReleaseTimeI2tEnd.Name[2Y8X_0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: ReleaseTimeI2tEnd

data.name: Property.ReleaseTimeI2tEnd.Definition[2Y8X_0qVeHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The release time in [s] for the end point of the I2 tripping curve of the G-function, if any. The value of ReleaseTimeI2tEnd shall be lower than ReleaseTimeI2tStart.
